==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Milk sickness
<hw>Milk sickness</hw>. <fld>(Veter., Med.)</fld> <def>A peculiar
malignant disease, occurring in parts of the western United States, and
affecting certain kinds of farm stock (esp. cows), and persons using the
meat or dairy products of infected cattle. Its chief symptoms in man are
uncontrollable vomiting, obstinate constipation, pain, and muscular
tremors. Its origin in cattle has been variously ascribed to the
presence of certain plants in their food, and to polluted
water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Milksop</ent>⟦br⟧
